sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/SDK
    participant UI as ml-pipeline-ui<br/>3000/TCP HTTP
    participant API as ml-pipeline<br/>(API Server)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow<br/>Controller
    participant Driver as kfp-driver<br/>(in pipeline pod)
    participant Launcher as kfp-launcher<br/>(in pipeline pod)
    participant MLMD as metadata-grpc-server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432 TCP
    participant S3 as MinIO/S3<br/>9000/443 TCP
    participant Cache as cache-server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant PA as persistence-agent
    participant SWF as scheduled-workflow<br/>controller

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Pipeline Run Execution

    User->>API: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    API->>DB: Store run metadata<br/>Optional TLS, User/Pass
    API->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>TLS, SA Token
    K8s->>Argo: Watch: new Workflow CR<br/>TLS, SA Token

    Note over Argo,Launcher: Pipeline Step Execution
    Argo->>Driver: Execute kfp-driver in pod
    Driver->>API: Resolve inputs<br/>8888/TCP HTTP, Bearer Token
    Driver->>MLMD: Log metadata<br/>8080/TCP gRPC, plaintext

    Note over K8s,Cache: Step Caching Check
    K8s->>Cache: Pod Admission Webhook<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    Cache->>DB: Check cache<br/>Optional TLS, User/Pass
    Cache-->>K8s: Allow/Mutate pod

    Launcher->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Access Key
    S3-->>Launcher: Artifact stored

    Note over PA,API: Status Synchronization
    PA->>K8s: Watch Workflow CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    K8s-->>PA: Workflow status updates
    PA->>API: Report run status<br/>8888/TCP HTTP, Bearer Token

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Scheduled/Recurring Run

    User->>API: POST /apis/v2beta1/recurringruns<br/>Bearer Token
    API->>K8s: Create ScheduledWorkflow CR<br/>TLS, SA Token
    SWF->>K8s: Watch ScheduledWorkflow CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    SWF->>K8s: Create Workflow (on schedule)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Frontend UI Access

    User->>UI: GET / (browser)<br/>3000/TCP HTTP plaintext
    UI->>API: API calls<br/>8888/TCP HTTP, SA Token
    UI->>S3: Fetch artifacts<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Access Key
    S3-->>UI: Artifact data
    UI-->>User: Rendered pipeline view
